just_use main.go

# label: VESTIGIAL (one-shot refactor tool)
# role: historical — Go-aware package mover

Batch Go package mover. Reads a `REORG` script of
`mv src/ dst/` lines and executes them as Go-aware package
moves: rewrites import paths across every `.go` file in the
repo, updates `package` declarations, then moves the
directories.

## Status (FIRM)

One-shot. Was built to support the 2026-early repo reorg
that relocated LynRummy and other packages into their current
nesting (`games/lynrummy/`, etc.). Not part of the regular
agent toolkit.

Kept for reference in case another reorg happens. If the
Go layout needs another shuffle, start by reading this
file's script format — but also audit the logic against
current `go/ast` + `go modules` behavior since tooling moves
fast.

## Usage

```
# Dry-run (default):
go run cmd/reorg/main.go REORG

# Apply for real:
go run cmd/reorg/main.go --execute REORG
```

REORG script format:

```
# Comments and blank lines ignored.
mv auth/ core/auth/
mv ratelimit/ internal/ratelimit/
```

Old and new import paths are inferred from the module name
in `go.mod`.

## Pointers

- Entry point: `main.main()`.
- Module layout as of today: see `go.mod` + the
  `games/`, `tools/`, `views/` tree.
